(83,	1,	'2018-11-04 06:06:48',	'2018-11-04 06:06:48',	'<blockquote>WEDNESDAY 16 MAY 2018\r\n\r\n<strong>â€œThereâ€™s nothing that captivates quite like the power of filmâ€</strong>\r\nâ€“ FlightNetwork</blockquote>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-10721 size-wide\" src=\"http://2018.hraff.org.au/wp-content/uploads/2018/05/hraff-opening-night-24-640x360.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"640\" height=\"360\" />\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>With the Melbourne leg of HRAFF concluding tomorrow, weâ€™re thrilled to be named the top film festival to attend byÂ <a href=\"https://www.flightnetwork.com.au/blog/australias-best-film-festivals-in-2018/\">FightNetwork!</a></strong>\r\n\r\n<em>As seen on their website:</em>\r\n<h6><strong>1. Human Rights Arts &amp; Film Festival â€“ MELBOURNE (May 3-17); LAUNCESTON (19-20); CANBERRA (May 29 â€“ June 5)</strong></h6>\r\n<h6><strong>The Festival</strong></h6>\r\nFeatured in various cities across Australia, this festival is dedicated to the brave storytellers whose films, music, and artwork shine a light on humanity in a way that is both thought-provoking, and thrilling. On average, nearly 17,000 people come out to this unique event over its course.\r\n<h6><strong>Know Before You Go</strong></h6>\r\nEach city that HRAFF finds itself in offers a different experience for visitorsâ€”Melbourne, for its coastal culture; Launceston, for its dedication to Tasmanian history; and Canberra, Australiaâ€™s capital, for its museums, and historic centre. Our recommendation: spend some time getting to knowÂ <a href=\"https://www.flightnetwork.com.au/\">the city</a>Â when youâ€™re there, by spending a day or two exploring each oneâ€™s many attractions. Single tickets cost $25, and you can find more informationÂ <a href=\"http://www.hraff.org.au/\">here</a>.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;',	'HRAFF HAS BEEN NAMED THE TOP FESTIVAL TO ATTEND BY FLYIGHTNETWORK AUSTRALIA',	'',	'publish',	'open',	'open',	'',	'hraff-has-been-named-the-top-festival',	'',	'',	'2018-11-